Oyindamola Bello is a young woman who recently finished her secondary school education. Unlike her mates who are engaged doing nothing or just doing social media, she turned into an entrepreneur and doing the business of selling noodles, pasta and other consumables in the Lekki area of Lagos State. In an interview with Daily Independent, she said that she was a beneficiary of the free-interest loan scheme that was powered by Chief Temitope Ajayi, the chairman of Chairman/CEO Silicon Valley Nigerian Economic Development (SV-NED). According to her, she got an initial interest-free loan of N20,000 from Chief Ajayi and started the business and when she paid back the loan she was given another N50,000 to expand the business. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The young entrepreneur said she loved doing business, adding that she planned to expand the business and open outlets in other areas of the state. According to her, the major challenge she faces is in the area of transport as she lives in Yaba and does business in Lekki; she stated that she spends hours in the traffic and pays high costs to drivers. I Want To Build A Food Village – Njarika People Should Not Be Afraid To Start Business In A Small Way – Bello She, however, said that the experience has been good and worthwhile, adding that she derived joy and satisfaction from contributing to the economic development of the community by rendering service to the people. Bello thanked Ajayi for providing her with the fund to start the business and that God will bless so that she will be a blessing to the youths of the country. Also speaking, Ajayi said that provided interest-free loans to people in the Lekki area to start or expand existing businesses because she realized that many Nigerian can do business, but they do not have the initial capital to start and she decided to step in and do something. The serial entrepreneur said she felt she had to do something with the resources at her disposal. The chairman of Chairman/CEO Silicon Valley Nigerian Economic Development has disbursed more than N10 million people in the Lekki area to start or expand existing businesses. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION